00037 double AbstractNavigationInterface::haversineDistance( double lat1, double lon1, double lat2, double lon2 ) {
00038         const double EARTH_RADIUS_AVERAGE = 6371009;//average earth radius in meters
00039 
00040         double deltalat = lat2 - lat1;
00041         double deltalon = lon2 - lon1;
00042 
00043         //convert from degree to radian
00044         deltalat *= M_PI/180.0;
00045         deltalon *= M_PI/180.0;
00046         lat1 *= M_PI/180.0;
00047         lat2 *= M_PI/180.0;
00048 
00049         //nasty spherical trig stuff
00050         double a = pow( sin( deltalat / 2 ), 2 ) +
00051                         cos(lat1) * cos(lat2) * pow( sin( deltalon / 2 ), 2 );
00052         double c = 2 * atan2( sqrt(a), sqrt(1-a) );
00053 
00054         return EARTH_RADIUS_AVERAGE * c;
00055 }

00057 double AbstractNavigationInterface::calcBearing( double lat1, double lon1, double lat2, double lon2, bool isDegrees ) {
00058         //convert inputs to radians
00059         lat1 *= M_PI/180.0;
00060         lon1 *= M_PI/180.0;
00061         lat2 *= M_PI/180.0;
00062         lon2 *= M_PI/180.0;
00063         double radBearing;
00064         double t1, t2, t3, t4, t5;
00065 
00066         //Do a bunch of magic trig
00067         t1 = sin(lat1) * sin(lat2);
00068         t2 = cos(lat1) * cos(lat2);
00069         t3 = cos(lon1 - lon2);
00070         t4 = t2 * t3;
00071         t5 = t1 + t4;
00072         double rad_dist = atan(-t5/sqrt(-t5*t5+1))+2*atan(1);
00073         t1 = sin(lat2) - sin(lat1) * cos(rad_dist);
00074         t2 = cos(lat1) * sin(rad_dist);
00075         t3 = t1/t2;
00076 
00077         if(sin(lon2 - lon1) < 0 ) {
00078                 t4 = atan(-t3/sqrt(-t3*t3+1)) + 2 * atan(1);
00079                 radBearing = t4;
00080         } else {
00081                 t4 = -t3 * t3 + 1;
00082                 t5 = 2 * M_PI - atan(-t3 / sqrt(-t3 * t3 + 1)) + 2 * atan(1);
00083                 radBearing = t5;
00084         }
00085         //convert outputs to degrees
00086         if( isDegrees ) radBearing *= 180.0/M_PI;
00087         return radBearing;
00088 }

00111 void TSPNavigation::nieveTSPSolution(  mrpt::aligned_containers<mrpt::poses::CPoint2D>::vector_t & toVisit,
00112                  mrpt::aligned_containers<mrpt::poses::CPoint2D>::vector_t & visited , bool inMeters) {
00113 
00114         while( toVisit.size() > 0 ) {
00115                 double shortestDistance = 10000000000000.0;//just a really big number
00116                 int closestIndex = 0;
00117                 for( unsigned index = 0; index < toVisit.size(); ++index ) {
00118                         double dist = haversineDistance( toVisit[index].m_coords[LAT], toVisit[index].m_coords[LON], visited.back().m_coords[LAT], visited.back().m_coords[LON] );
00119                         if(shortestDistance > dist && dist > .1 ) {     //if the distance is really really small we must be checking the same point
00120                                 closestIndex = index;                                   //besides the gps isn't accurate to a tenth of a meter
00121                                 shortestDistance = dist;                                //however there ought to be a better way then this and it should be fixed
00122                         }
00123                 }
00124                 mrpt::poses::CPoint2D& point = (toVisit[closestIndex]);
00125                 if(inMeters)
00126                 {
00127                         int multx = point.m_coords[LON] > visited.front().m_coords[LON] ? 1 : -1;
00128                         int multy = point.m_coords[LAT] > visited.front().m_coords[LAT] ? 1 : -1;
00129                         point.m_coords[LAT] = multy * (haversineDistance( visited.front().m_coords[LAT],toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LON],
00130                                         toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LAT], toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LON] ));
00131                         point.m_coords[LON] = multx * (haversineDistance( toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LAT], visited.front().m_coords[LON],
00132                                         toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LAT], toVisit[closestIndex].m_coords[LON] ));
00133                 }
00134                 visited.push_back(toVisit[closestIndex]);
00135                 toVisit.erase(toVisit.begin()+closestIndex);
00136 
00137         }
00138         if(inMeters){
00139                 visited.front().m_coords[LAT] = 0;
00140                 visited.front().m_coords[LON] = 0;
00141         }
00142         mrpt::poses::CPoint2D finish = mrpt::poses::CPoint2D();
00143         visited.push_back(finish);
